title: 1950 United States Senate elections
added: In these cases, the incumbent or appointee lost renomination, but the party managed to retain the seat in the general election.

#[[#North Carolina (Special)|North Carolina (Special)]]: Appointee [[Frank Porter Graham]] lost nomination to finish the term, while nominee [[Willis Smith]] won the general election to serve out the term.
#[[#Florida|Florida]]: Incumbent [[Claude Pepper]] lost an exceptionally nasty primary to [[George Smathers]], who won the general election.
#[[#Oklahoma|Oklahoma]]: Incumbent [[Elmer Thomas]] lost the primary to [[Mike Monroney]], who won the general election.
#[[#South Dakota|South Dakota]]: Incumbent [[John Chandler Gurney]] lost the primary to [[Francis H. Case]], who won the general election.
